cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with the ability of artificial neural networks to learn structural relationships and generalize knowledge to new situations. This is a common theme in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL), which falls under the cs.CL sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning (ML) techniques, which are covered by cs.LG and cs.AI. Neural networks are a type of ML model that can be used for a variety of tasks, including image recognition, which falls under cs.CV. Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural decoding techniques to understand what the networks have learned, which is related to the field of computational neuroscience (cs.NE).
